9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 379, L.D. 611, “An Act to Allow the
10 Secretary of State to Collect Excise Taxes on Motor Vehicles Owned by Residents Who
11 Are Unhoused”
12 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the enacting clause and inserting the
13 following:
14 'Sec. 1. 36 MRSA §1484, sub-§3, ¶A, as amended by PL 2007, c. 627, §33, is
15 further amended to read:
16 A. The excise tax on a motor vehicle owned by an individual resident of this State
17 must be paid in the place where the owner resides. If the individual resident of this
18 State does not have a residing place, the excise tax may be paid directly to the Secretary
19 of State if:
20 (1) The motor vehicle was previously registered in this State to the individual
21 resident;
22 (2) The Secretary of State confirms with the municipality where the individual
23 resides that the municipality refused to receive the excise tax of the individual who
24 does not have a residing place; and
25 (3) The individual resident holds a license pursuant to Title 29-A, section 1251.'
26 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
27 number to read consecutively.
28 SUMMARY
2299 This amendment specifies that a resident of the State who does not have a residing
3300 place may pay the excise tax directly to the Secretary of State if the resident is renewing
3311 the motor vehicle registration, the Secretary of State has confirmed with the municipality
